# UTC Time Standard Rules

## Purpose
Enforce one time standard (UTC) across the whole project.

## Core Rules
- All persisted timestamps must use UTC semantics.
- Database timestamp columns must use `TIMESTAMPTZ`.
- Application clock providers must return UTC.
- Logger timestamps must be UTC.
- Container runtime timezone must be UTC (`TZ=UTC`).

## Implementation Rules
- Use centralized clock providers (do not call local time directly in business logic).
- Normalize times at adapter boundaries when reading from external systems.
- Keep DB session timezone set to UTC from persistence initialization.

## API/Contract Rules
- Return times in RFC3339-compatible UTC format when exposed externally.
- Avoid locale-specific time rendering in API payloads.

## Testing Rules
- Tests must be deterministic and timezone-safe.
- Use explicit UTC timestamps in fixtures and assertions.
